title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out of sync (1GILQD5)
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported JAR in the same directory (project), an out of sync message is displayed when overwriting the exported JAR file for the second time.
EB: The system should not display an out of sync message when overwriting the exported JAR file in the same directory.
SR:
To reproduce:
1. Open the project and select the Export option.
2. Choose the directory to export and proceed with the export.
3. Place the exported JAR in the same directory.
4. Repeat the export process by overwriting the existing JAR file.
5. Observe the out of sync message.
